main event: A civilian observed a cigar-shaped object with changing colors over Othello, Washington on March 30, 1967.
interesting points: The object changed color from white to red to green.
The object had a whirring sound, though some witnesses reported no sound.
Multiple military personnel from the 637th Radar Squadron witnessed the object.
The object was estimated to be the size of a baseball at 10,000 feet altitude.
The object moved straight at an estimated speed of 2,000 mph before disappearing.
witnesses: civilian and military personnel from the 637th Radar Squadron
